@* BOUNDARY for decision 160: a computed over a structurally MUTATED List is refused -- its
   reactivity lives in a version signal the computed's body never reads, so computed() would
   evaluate once and go silently stale. The remedy is the Duel's split (a reassigned view). *@

<p id="out">@Total</p>
<button id="b" @onclick="Go">go</button>

@code {
    private List<int> xs = new List<int> { 1, 2 };

    private int Total => xs.Count;

    void Go()
    {
        xs.Add(3);
    }
}
